REQP-1725#1 Advisory
DSP_Abus_sign_bit_alert  
design_1_i/stream_matmul_0/inst/grp_stream_matmul_Pipeline_VITIS_LOOP_83_8_VITIS_LOOP_84_9_VITIS_LOOP_87_10_fu_165/fadd_32ns_32ns_32_5_full_dsp_1_U18/stream_matmul_fadd_32ns_32ns_32_5_full_dsp_1_ip_u/U0/i_synth/ADDSUB_OP.ADDSUB/DSP.OP/DSP48E1_BODY.ALIGN_ADD/DSP2/i_no_versal_es1_workaround.DSP: When using the PreAdder and USE_DPORT is TRUE, the A operand should be restricted to 24 bit two's complement (and sign extended) to avoid over/underflow in the pre-add stage.
Related violations: <none>


